# Site version bump (footer)

The public site version comes from **`package.json`** → **`src/lib/site-version.ts`** → footer (`Footer.astro`). Users and operators treat it as the deploy label.

## When to bump

Run **`./scripts/bump-patch-version.sh`** (patch +1) **once per delivery** whenever you change anything that ships in the Astro site:

- `src/**` (components, views, pages, i18n, content, lib)
- `astro.config.mjs`, `public/**`, `nginx/**` used by the container
- Blog posts under `src/content/doc/**`

**Do not skip** because the change was “small”, docs-only inside `src/content/doc/`, or done in direct IDE chat instead of autoagents.

**Skip the bump** only when the diff is limited to `autoagents/`, `.cursor/`, root docs (`docs/`, `README.md`), or other files that never affect the built site.

## How

```bash
./scripts/bump-patch-version.sh   # prints e.g. 1.1.5 → 1.1.6
```

Include the updated `package.json` in the same commit as the product change. Never edit the version string by hand unless fixing a mistake.

## Verify

After `docker compose build && docker compose up -d`, confirm the footer shows the new semver (all locales). Optionally:

```bash
curl -s http://127.0.0.1:9180/ | grep -o 'Versión [0-9.]*\|Version [0-9.]*\|Versió [0-9.]*'
```

## autoagents

Coder steps (FEAT/NEW → UNTESTED) and the committer role must enforce the same rule; see also `.cursor/rules/autoagents-workflow.mdc`.
